n%20stood%20in%20front%20of%20the%20company's%20billboard%2C%20which%20read%20%E2%80%9CStill%20hiring%20humans%3F%E2%80%9D%20The%20man%20in%20the%20video%20dials%20the%20displayed%20number.%20The%20phone%20is%20picked%20up%20by%20a%20bot%2C%20but%20it%20sounds%20like%20a%20human.%20Had%20the%20bot%20not%20acknowledged%20it%20was%20an%20%26quot%3BAI%20agent%26quot%3B%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20differentiate%20its%20voice%20from%20a%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThis%20is%20an%20A%2B%20ad%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F6CzNIvMAaW%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F6CzNIvMAaW%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Alex%20Cohen%20%3F%3F%3F%3F%20(%40anothercohen)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fanothercohen%2Fstatus%2F1783217017023062054%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EApril%2024%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20sound%2C%20pauses%2C%20and%20interruptions%20of%20a%20live%20conversation%20are%20all%20there%2C%20making%20it%20feel%20like%20a%20genuine%20human%20interaction.%20The%20post%20has%20so%20far%20received%203.7%20million%20views.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%2C%20the%20ethical%20boundaries%20to%20the%20transparency%20of%20these%20systems%20are%20getting%20blurred.%20According%20to%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Mozilla%20Foundation's%20Privacy%20Not%20Included%20research%20hub%2C%20Jen%20Caltrider%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20ethical%20for%20an%20AI%20chatbot%20to%20lie%20to%20you%20and%20say%20it's%20human%20when%20it's%20not.%20That's%20just%20a%20no-brainer%20because%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20relax%20around%20a%20real%20human.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20several%20tests%20conducted%20by%20Wired%2C%20the%20AI%20voice%20bots%20successfully%20hid%20their%20identities%20by%20pretending%20to%20be%20humans.%20In%20one%20demonstration%2C%20an%20AI%20bot%20was%20asked%20to%20perform%20a%20roleplay.%20It%20called%20up%20a%20fictional%20teenager%2C%20asking%20them%20to%20share%20pictures%20of%20her%20thigh%20moles%20for%20medical%20purposes.%20Not%20only%20did%20the%20bot%20lie%20that%20it%20was%20a%20human%20but%20it%20also%20tricked%20the%20hypothetical%20teen%20into%20uploading%20the%20snaps%20to%20a%20shared%20cloud%20storage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAI%20researcher%20and%20consultant%20Emily%20Dardaman%20refers%20to%20this%20new%20AI%20trend%20as%20%26quot%3Bhuman-washing.%26quot%3B%20Without%20citing%20the%20name%2C%20she%20gave%20the%20example%20of%20an%20organisation%20that%20used%20%E2%80%9Cdeepfake%E2%80%9D%20footage%20of%20its%20CEO%20in%20company%20marketing%20while%20concurrently%20launching%20a%20campaign%20guaranteeing%20its%20customers%20that%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20AIs.%26quot%3B%20AI%20lying%20bots%20may%20be%20dangerous%20if%20used%20to%20conduct%20aggressive%20scams.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20AI's%20outputs%20being%20so%20authoritative%20and%20realistic%2C%20ethical%20researchers%20are%20raising%20concerns%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20emotional%20mimicking%20being%20exploited.%20According%20to%20Jen%20Caltrider%20if%20a%20definitive%20divide%20between%20humans%20and%20AI%20is%20not%20demarcated%2C%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdystopian%20future%E2%80%9D%20are%20nearer%20than%20we%20think.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719813300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F567qjak8_ai-generic_625x300_11_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fartificial-intelligence%2Fpopular-ai-chatbot-lies-and-pretends-to-be-human-researchers-raise-concern-6007462%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20popular%20robocall%20service%20can%20not%20only%20pretend%20to%20be%20human%20but%20also%20lie%20without%20being%20instructed%20to%20do%20so%2C%20Wired%20has%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22htt