e%20mondain%2C%20and%20to%20the%20plebian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUruguayan%20writer%20Eduardo%20Galeano's%20masterpiece%20on%20football%2C%20%3Cem%3ESoccer%20in%20Sun%20and%20Shadow%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20is%20a%20one-stop%20shop%20for%20those%20meaning%20to%20explore%20the%20power%20of%20sports.%20%26quot%3BTell%20me%20how%20you%20play%20and%20I'll%20tell%20you%20who%20you%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Galeano.%20His%20explorations%20of%20'soccer'%20in%20Latin%20America%20reveal%20everything%20about%20the%20region's%20past%2C%20present%2C%20and%20even%20future.%20Soccer%20is%20inextricably%20linked%20to%20the%20Latin%20American%20identity%20as%20cricket%20is%20to%20the%20South%20Asian.%20There's%20something%20primordial%20about%20it.%20We%20do%20not%20really%20see%20it%20in%20the%20so-called%20'first%20world'.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20author%20had%20her%20worst%20sports%20experience%20in%20a%20city%20in%20Scotland%20-%20a%20country%20with%20an%20international%20cricket%20team.%20There's%20nothing%20worse%20than%20being%20the%20only%20person%20familiar%20with%20cricket%20in%20a%20country%20that%20has%20played%20cricket%20for%20more%20than%20two%20centuries.%20The%20saltiness%20of%20India's%20defeat%20in%20the%20ICC%20ODI%20World%20Cup%20(men)%20final%20was%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20colonisers%2C%20who%20brought%20us%20the%20sport%2C%20have%20moved%20on%20totally%20and%20completely.%20They%20do%20not%20see%20it%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20wield%20their%20power%3B%20it's%20up%20to%20the%20Brave%20New%20World%20to%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%20with%20cricket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENever%20Just%20A%20Game%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECaribbean%20writer%20CLR%20James%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EBeyond%20a%20Boundary%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20can%20be%20raw%20pain%20and%20bleeding%20where%20so%20many%20thousands%20see%20the%20inevitable%20ups%20and%20downs%20of%20only%20a%20game.%26quot%3B%20For%20countries%20like%20India%2C%20cricket%20can%20never%20be%20just%20a%20game%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20loud%20the%20cynics%20shout%20from%20their%20ivory%20towers.%20A%20cricket%20win%20or%20loss%20has%20consequences%20for%20those%20who%20are%20not%20even%20in%20the%20stadium%2C%20physically%20or%20metaphorically.%20West%20Indies-it's%20not%20a%20country-predicated%20its%20unity%20principle%20on%20the%20power%20of%20cricket.%20It%20cannot%20be%20trivialised%20as%20%26quot%3Bjust%20a%20game%26quot%3B.%20An%20acknowledgement%20of%20its%20power%20is%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20rescuing%20it%20from%20the%20ills%20that%20power%20breeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20total%20contrast%20with%20Plato's%20conceptualisation%20of%20sports%20-%20a%20means%20to%20the%20end%20of%20personal%20virtue%2C%20intellectual%20prowess%2C%20and%20socio-political%20harmony%20-%20victory%20does%20not%20necessarily%20have%20a%20sobering%20impact%20on%20a%20people.%20Scholars%20like%20Ria%20Ivandi%C4%87%2C%20Tom%20Kirchmaier%2C%20Yasaman%20Saeidi%2C%20and%20Neus%20Torres%20Blas%20have%20recently%20demonstrated%20how%20%26quot%3Bin%20sum%2C%20across%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20sports%20and%20contexts%2C%20domestic%20abuse%20is%20shown%20to%20increase%20following%20a%20game%26quot%3B.%20Yes%2C%20there%20may%20be%20public%20scenes%20of%20celebrations%20with%20all%20the%20generations%20partaking%20in%20the%20glory%20of%20an%20elusive%20defeat.%20There%20may%20be%20momentary%20egalitarianism%20manifesting%20in%20high-fiving%20between%20the%20Porsche-driving%20elite%20and%20the%20balloon-selling%20vendors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Dramatic%20Victory%2C%20A%20Terrible%20Beauty%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere's%20nothing%20more%20satisfying%20than%20a%20dramatic%20victory.%20%26quot%3BTo%20win%20without%20magic%2C%20without%20surprise%20or%20beauty%2C%20isn't%20that%20worse%20than%20losing%3F%26quot%3B%20Galeano%20says%20so%20about%20football%20victories.%20With%20a%20dramatic%20sports%20victory%2C%20a%20terrible%20beauty%20is%20born.%20How%20much%20terror%20it%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20unleash%20is%20a%20matter%20for%20a%20functioning%20republic%20to%20assess.%20India%20has%20recognised%20the%20potential%20of%20cricket%20to%20nurture%20a%20national%20identity%20-%20career%20politicians%20have%20actively%20engaged%20with%20the%20sport's%20management%20and%20exploited%20its%20promise.%20Cricketers%20have%20dabbled%20in%20realpolitik%2C%20too.%20It's%20all%20fair%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20present%20moment%20of%20cricketing%20glory%20has%20come%20from%20Barbados.%20It%20is%20the%20place%20where%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20controversies%2C%20with%20overlaps%20of%20colonialism%2C%20identity%2C%20and%20cricket%20erupted%20twenty-five%20years%20ago.%20Lloyd%20Barker%2C%20a%20West%20Indian%20umpire%2C%20was%20accused%20by%20BBC%20correspondent%20Christopher%20Martin%20Jenkins%20of%20capitulating%20under%20West%20Indies%20captain%20Viv%20Richards's%20appeal%20and%20wrongly%20dismissing%20Robert%20Bailey%20during%20the%20England-West%20Indies%20Test%20series%20in%201990.%20Barbados%20erupted%20in%20protest%20against%20this%20affront%20to%20the%20Caribbean%20culture%20and%20character.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20cricket%20in%20India%20must%20undertake%20what%20Galeano%20says%20in%20the%20context%20of%20football%3A%20%26quot%3Ba%20sad%20voyage%20from%20beauty%20to%20duty%26quot%3B.%20India%20has%20a%20duty%20to%20-%20and%20only%20India%20can%20-%20%C2%A0protect%20cricket's%20beauty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Nishtha%20Gautam%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20author%20and%20academic.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719813180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fk2fjidvg_india-t20-wc_625x300_30_June_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fworld-cup-cricket-p