-124070100092_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ITR%20Filing%202024%20Deadline%3A%20Penalty%20For%20Missing%20The%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20Filing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20income%20tax%20return%20is%20a%20summarized%20document%20that%20outlines%20a%20taxpayer's%20earnings%20over%20a%20fiscal%20year.%20If%20an%20individual%20fails%20to%20file%20their%20income%20tax%20return%2C%20they%20will%20incur%20a%20penalty.%20The%20Income%20Tax%20department%20has%20different%20tax%20rates%20for%20various%20income%20brackets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20department%20also%20sends%20reminders%20to%20encourage%20the%20timely%20filing%20of%20income%20tax%20returns.%20Non-compliance%2C%20such%20as%20failing%20to%20meet%20obligations%20or%20neglecting%20to%20file%20an%20ITR%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20fines%20and%20penalties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20financial%20year%20ending%20on%20March%2031%2C%202024%2C%20the%20deadline%20for%20individuals%20to%20submit%20their%20Income%20Tax%20Returns%20(ITRs)%20is%20July%2031%2C%202024.%20However%2C%20filing%20ITRs%20can%20be%20a%20complex%20process%2C%20particularly%20for%20individual%20taxpayers%20who%20might%20struggle%20with%20the%20various%20schedules%20and%20disclosures%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGathering%20all%20necessary%20information%20and%20maintaining%20records%20of%20expenses%20from%20the%20previous%20year%20can%20be%20challenging%2C%20often%20resulting%20in%20missed%20deadlines.%20Consequently%2C%20many%20individuals%20may%20require%20additional%20time%20to%20complete%20their%20tax%20returns%20to%20avoid%20adverse%20actions%20from%20the%20Income%20Tax%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Income%20Tax%20Department%20allows%20taxpayers%20who%20miss%20the%20original%20deadline%20to%20file%20a%20belated%20return%20by%20December%2031%20of%20the%20same%20calendar%20year.%20Thus%2C%20the%20deadline%20for%20filing%20a%20belated%20return%20for%20AY%202024-25%20is%20December%2031%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPenalty%20On%20Delayed%20ITR%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20taxpayer%20files%20a%20belated%20income%20tax%20return%2C%20they%20may%20incur%20penalties%20based%20on%20their%20income%20level.%20A%20penalty%20of%20Rs.%201%2C000%20applies%20if%20the%20income%20is%20below%20Rs.%205%2C00%2C000%2C%20while%20a%20penalty%20of%20Rs.%205%2C000%20is%20enforced%20if%20the%20income%20exceeds%20Rs.%205%2C00%2C000.%20Additionally%2C%20late%20filers%20might%20face%20interest%20charges%20and%20lose%20certain%20benefits%20typically%20enjoyed%20by%20timely%20filers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnsuring%20tax%20compliance%20is%20crucial%2C%20as%20it%20is%20a%20legal%20obligation%20that%20taxpayers%20must%20adhere%20to.%20Responsible%20financial%20practices%20are%20essential%20for%20a%20seamless%20and%20trouble-free%20tax%20filing%20process.%20For%20further%20insights%20into%20the%20consequences%20of%20delayed%20income%20tax%20return%20submissions%20and%20options%20for%20requesting%20extensions%2C%20please%20find%20detailed%20information%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20provisions%20specified%20in%20section%20234F%20of%20The%20Income%20Tax%20Act%2C%20individuals%20who%20file%20their%20Income%20Tax%20Returns%20(ITR)%20after%20the%20due%20date%20are%20subject%20to%20a%20late%20filing%20penalty.%20The%20maximum%20penalty%20for%20late%20filing%20has%20been%20revised%20to%20Rs.%205%2C000%20starting%20from%20the%20Financial%20Year%202021%2C%20down%20from%20the%20previous%20limit%20of%20Rs.%2010%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20taxpayers%20are%20advised%20to%20adhere%20to%20the%20filing%20deadlines%2C%20as%20missing%20the%20deadline%20can%20result%20in%20not%20just%20the%20late%20filing%20penalty%20but%20also%20other%20penalties%20and%20restrictions%20enforced%20by%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20individuals%20with%20a%20total%20income%20of%20INR%205%20lakh%20or%20less%2C%20the%20late%20filing%20penalty%20is%20capped%20at%20Rs.%201%2C000%2C%20offering%20some%20relief%20to%20small%20taxpayers.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20individuals%20with%20higher%20incomes%20may%20be%20liable%20to%20pay%20the%20full%20penalty%20of%20Rs.%205%2C000%20if%20they%20fail%20to%20file%20their%20ITR%20within%20the%20specified%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20interest%20on%20unpaid%20taxes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELate%20filers%20may%20incur%20penalties%20and%20owe%20interest%20on%20unpaid%20taxes%20as%20specified%20under%20Section%20234A%20of%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act.%20The%20interest%20rate%20is%20currently%201%25%20per%20month%20or%20part%20thereof%2C%20calculated%20from%20the%20day%20after%20the%20ITR%20filing%20deadline.%20This%20interest%20is%20intended%20to%20discourage%20delayed%20tax%20payments%20and%20encourage%20prompt%20compliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20timely%20processing%20of%20government%20refunds%20for%20overpaid%20taxes%2C%20taxpayers%20should%20submit%20their%20ITRs%20before%20the%20deadline.%20Missing%20the%20deadline%20may%20lead%20to%20extended%20waits%20for%20refunds%2C%20potentially%20causing%20financial%20difficulties%20and%20cash%20flow%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EExemptions%20from%20Penalty%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20an%20individual's%20taxable%20income%20is%20below%20the%20basic%20exemption%20limit%20and%20they%20file%20an%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20(ITR)%20to%20claim%20a%20refund%2C%20they%20are%20not%20subject%20to%20a%20penalty%20for%20late%20filing.%20The%20basic%20exemption%20limit%20refers%20to%20the%20gross%20taxable%20income%20before%20any%20deductions%20are%20applied.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719803880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fmgqjpacg_itr-efiling-istock_625x300_27_June_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fitr-filing-2024-deadline-penalty-for-missing-the-income-tax-return-filing-6006821%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Inc